---
import MarketingLayout from "../layouts/MarketingLayout.astro";
import SiteHeader from "../components/SiteHeader.astro";
import SiteFooter from "../components/SiteFooter.astro";
import { siteConfig } from "../config/site";
---

<MarketingLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | Qwerio"
  description="Privacy policy explaining how Qwerio collects, uses, and protects data."
  canonicalPath="/privacy"
>
  <SiteHeader />

  <main class="container legal-wrap">
    <article class="legal-doc panel">
      <header class="legal-header">
        <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p>
          Last updated: <strong>{siteConfig.lastUpdated}</strong>
        </p>
      </header>

      <section>
        <h2>1. Scope</h2>
        <p>
          This Privacy Policy explains how {siteConfig.companyName} ("we", "us") handles personal
          information when you use {siteConfig.siteName} websites and services.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>Depending on usage, we may collect:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Account and contact data, such as name and email.</li>
          <li>Operational telemetry, logs, and device/browser metadata.</li>
          <li>Support communications and issue reports.</li>
          <li>Billing and subscription metadata where applicable.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>3. How We Use Information</h2>
        <p>We process information to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Provide, maintain, and improve the Services.</li>
          <li>Authenticate access, secure systems, and prevent abuse.</li>
          <li>Respond to support requests and service notices.</li>
          <li>Meet legal, compliance, and contractual obligations.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>4. Data Processing and Security</h2>
        <p>
          We use reasonable administrative, technical, and organizational safeguards designed to
          protect information. No method of transmission or storage is completely secure, and we
          cannot guarantee absolute security.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>5. Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
        <p>
          We do not sell personal information. We may share data with service providers, professional
          advisors, or authorities when required for service delivery, legal compliance, or rights
          protection.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
        <p>
          We retain information for as long as needed to provide the Services, resolve disputes,
          enforce agreements, and comply with legal obligations.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>7. International Transfers</h2>
        <p>
          If data is transferred across jurisdictions, we apply safeguards required by applicable
          privacy laws and contractual commitments.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>8. Your Rights</h2>
        <p>
          Depending on your location, you may have rights to access, correct, delete, or restrict
          processing of your personal information. You may also have rights related to portability
          and objection.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>9. Cookies and Similar Technologies</h2>
        <p>
          We may use cookies or similar technologies for essential functionality, analytics, and
          performance optimization. You can manage cookie controls through your browser settings.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>10. Children’s Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          The Services are not directed to children under the age required by local law. If you
          believe a child has provided personal data, contact us to request deletion.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>11. Policy Changes</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Material changes will be reflected by
          revising the "Last updated" date.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>12. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          For privacy requests or questions, contact
          <a href={`mailto:${siteConfig.contactEmail}`}>{siteConfig.contactEmail}</a>.
        </p>
      </section>
    </article>
  </main>

  <SiteFooter />
</MarketingLayout>
